Package com.lugowoy.helper.filling.array.numbers

Class FillingArrayReadDoubleNumbers

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.lugowoy.helper.filling.FillingReadValues
      • com.lugowoy.helper.filling.array.FillingArrayReadValues<java.lang.Double>
        • com.lugowoy.helper.filling.array.numbers.FillingArrayReadDoubleNumbers
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    FillingArray<java.lang.Double>, FillingArrayNumbers<java.lang.Double>, Filling<Array<java.lang.Double>>
    public class FillingArrayReadDoubleNumbers
extends FillingArrayReadValues<java.lang.Double>
implements FillingArrayNumbers<java.lang.Double>
    The class provides functionality to fill an object of the Array class and classical arrays with data of the Double type with read by the Reader class object encapsulated in the parent class FillingArrayReadValues. The class is the heir of the FillingArrayReadValues class and implements it's contract. Also implements the contract declared by the FillingArrayNumbers interface.

    Created by Konstantin Lugowoy on 08-Jan-18.

    Version:
    1.4
    Author:
    Konstantin Lugowoy
    See Also:
    FillingArrayReadValues, Filling, FillingArray, FillingArrayNumbers

        public java.lang.Double[] fill​(int lengthArray)
        Fills an array with data of the Double type with read by the Reader class object.

        The array is created based on the "lengthArray" parameter. The parameter "lengthArray" determines the length(size) of the created array. If the value of "lengthArray" is less than "0" or is greatest than "32767", created array of length Array.DEFAULT_LENGTH_ARRAY.

      • fill

        public void fill​(Array<java.lang.Double> array,
                 java.lang.Double startBound,
                 java.lang.Double endBound)
          throws java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        Fills an object of the Array class with data of the Double type with read by the Reader class object.

        The object of the Array class is filled with numeric data from the value "startBound" to the value of the "endBound" parameters. If the value of the argument "startBound" is greater than the value of "endBound" or if one of the arguments is in the range from -32768 to 32768, then the values DefaultValuesForFilling.DEFAULT_DOUBLE_NEGATIVE_BOUND and DefaultValuesForFilling.DEFAULT_DOUBLE_POSITIVE_BOUND respectively.

        Specified by:
        fill in interface FillingArrayNumbers<java.lang.Double>
        Parameters:
        array - The object of the Array class that must be filled with data of the Double type with read by the Reader class object.
        startBound - The value of the start bound for filling an object of the Array class with data of the Double type with read by the Reader class object.
        endBound - The value of the end bound for filling an object of the Array class with data of the Double type with read by the Reader class object.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - If the object argument is null.
